modules.description: This module parses and generates JSON values with safe error handling, converting between JSON syntax and OCaml values. It handles input from strings, files, or channels, and supports pretty-printing, equality checks, and custom output formatting. Use cases include reading configuration files, serializing data structures, or exchanging structured data in network protocols.

This module parses and serializes JSON values to and from strings, files, and channels, supporting structured data interchange. It operates on the `Yojson_five.Basic.t` type, representing JSON values like objects, arrays, numbers, and strings. Use cases include reading JSON configuration files, transmitting JSON data over network streams, or pretty-printing JSON for debugging.

This module provides functions for parsing and serializing JSON data with safe error handling and customizable output formatting. It operates on JSON values represented as the `t` type, supporting structured data interchange through strings, files, and channels. Concrete use cases include reading configuration files, transmitting JSON over network protocols, and debugging via pretty-printing.
